{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17537274","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17537274"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:15:43+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:15:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16017"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16017","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16017"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.45,0.34,0.15,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8708"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107090"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8708","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8708"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16017"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89554"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"36"},{"type":"tags","id":"37"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"191"},{"type":"tags","id":"1745"},{"type":"tags","id":"2038"},{"type":"tags","id":"2182"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"3511"},{"type":"tags","id":"3976"},{"type":"tags","id":"4195"},{"type":"tags","id":"4681"},{"type":"tags","id":"4970"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4983"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11643"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20831"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35675"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44657"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107090","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107090"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 68-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a six-month history of reduced libido and fatigue. He has noticed decreased morning erections with occasional difficulty maintaining erections. He reports that whilst his weight itself has been stable, he seems to be losing muscle mass and gaining fat around his abdomen despite maintaining his usual exercise routine. He has hypertension managed with amlodipine. He does not take any other medications. He is a non-smoker and drinks alcohol occasionally.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. His body mass index is 31 kg/m\u00b2. Digital rectal examination reveals a normal-sized, smooth prostate. Two morning testosterone levels taken two weeks apart are 7.4 nmol/L (10.0-35.0) and 6.8 nmol/L. Prostate specific antigen is 2.1 \u00b5g/L (\u0026lt;4.0). Full blood count, renal function, and liver function tests are within normal limits.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Repeat testosterone level in six months","Testosterone replacement therapy","Weight loss to achieve normal body mass index and increase exercise","Sildenafil","Clomiphene citrate"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with clinical features of testosterone deficiency (reduced libido, fatigue, decreased morning erections, reduced muscle mass) and has two confirmed low morning testosterone levels. The diagnosis of age-related testosterone deficiency requires both symptoms and biochemical confirmation with two morning testosterone measurements below the reference range.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWeight loss to achieve normal body mass index and increasing exercise\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate first-line management. Obesity is associated with reduced testosterone levels, and weight loss has been shown to improve both testosterone levels and symptoms. Given this patient\u0027s BMI of 31 kg/m\u00b2, lifestyle modification should be attempted before considering hormone replacement. Additionally, whilst his testosterone levels are below the reference range, this is common for older men and guidelines recommend that men with testosterone \u0026gt;6 nmol/L should have correction of other contributory factors prior to initiation of testosterone therapy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETestosterone replacement therapy\u003C/strong\u003E may be appropriate, but this patient should first correct his weight which may be contributing to his low testosterone levels. While the patient meets diagnostic criteria with symptoms and biochemical confirmation, guidelines recommend attempting lifestyle modifications first, particularly in obese patients, before initiating hormone replacement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EClomiphene citrate\u003C/strong\u003E can be used for male infertility and to stimulate testosterone production in younger men. It is not appropriate for age-related testosterone deficiency in older men.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESildenafil\u003C/strong\u003E addresses erectile dysfunction specifically but would not address his low libido or the underlying testosterone deficiency or its other manifestations such as reduced muscle mass and fatigue.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERepeat testosterone level in six months\u003C/strong\u003E without intervention would unnecessarily delay management where lifestyle changes can be recommended initially. Following these changes, a repeat level should be performed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf lifestyle modifications do not lead to improvement after 3-6 months, testosterone replacement therapy could then be considered, with appropriate monitoring of clinical response, testosterone levels, haematocrit, and PSA.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Diagnosis of testosterone deficiency requires both clinical symptoms and confirmed low morning testosterone levels on two separate occasions.","Lifestyle modifications including weight loss and exercise are first-line management for mild testosterone deficiency in obese men.","Testosterone replacement therapy should only be considered after lifestyle modifications have been attempted."],"references":["Kanakis GA, Pofi R, Goulis DG, Isidori AM, Armeni E, Erel CT, et al. EMAS position statement: Testosterone replacement therapy in older men. Maturitas. 2023 Dec 1;178:107854. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37845136/","Yeap BB, Grossmann M, McLachlan RI, Handelsman DJ, Wittert GA, Conway AJ, et al. Endocrine Society of Australia position statement on male hypogonadism (part 2): treatment and therapeutic considerations. Medical Journal of Australia. 2016 Sep;205(5):228\u201331. Available at: https://www.mja.com.au/system/files/issues/205_05/10.5694mja16.00448.pdf","Androgen deficiency in older men. Australian Journal of General Practice. 2023. Available at: https://www1.racgp.org.au/ajgp/2019/july/androgen-deficiency-in-older-men"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89554"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16017"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89554","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89554"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-25T07:03:47+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-25T07:03:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8708"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107090"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"rel